ak\n            else:\n                current_streak = 0\n        \n        return count\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the array, keeping track of the current streak of consecutive zeros. For each zero encountered, it increments the current streak and adds it to the count. When a non-zero is encountered, the current streak is reset to zero. This approach ensures that all subarrays filled with zeros are counted efficiently.", "estimated_date": 1658016000000}